        },
        {
            "text": "With this ansatz, \u03c7 2 is given by",
            "section": "III. FIT RESULTS",
            "paragraph_rank": 29,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "where\u0177 is the measured vector of observables, and the weight matrix G is taken to be",
            "section": "III. FIT RESULTS",
            "paragraph_rank": 30,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "where C stat (y) and C sys (y) are the statistical and systematic covariance matrices, respectively. ",
            "section": "III. FIT RESULTS",
            "paragraph_rank": 31,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "The minimum of \u03c7 2 is reached for",
            "section": "III. FIT RESULTS",
            "paragraph_rank": 31,
