                },
                {
                    "start": 80,
                    "end": 84,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b34",
                    "text": "[22]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The results of all four favor cos 2\u03b2 > 0, and in Ref. ",
            "section": "III. FIT RESULTS",
            "paragraph_rank": 35,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "[22] cos 2\u03b2 < 0 is excluded with 4.5 \u03c3 significance.",
            "section": "III. FIT RESULTS",
            "paragraph_rank": 35,
            "section_rank": 4,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 4,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b34",
                    "text": "[22]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "In the second step, we fix the two \u03bb values according to the p 1 and p 2 results of the first step, i.e. to the central values in Eqs. ",
            "section": "III. FIT RESULTS",
            "paragraph_rank": 36,
