                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b19",
                    "text": "[7]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "For both simulations we use Im (\u03bb) = 0.67 and Re (\u03bb) = \u22120.74 and sample t values between 0 and +5/\u0393. ",
            "section": "IV. ESTIMATING THE INFLUENCE OF \u2206\u0393",
            "paragraph_rank": 40,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "We then fit the two samples, binned in intervals of \u2206t = 0.25/\u0393, to the expressions N e \u2212\u0393t [1 + C cos(\u2206m t) + S sin(\u2206m t)] ,",
            "section": "IV. ESTIMATING THE INFLUENCE OF \u2206\u0393",
            "paragraph_rank": 40,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "with three free parameters N , C and S. The fit results agree between the two simulations within 0.002 for C and 0.008 for S. We, therefore, conclude that omission of the sinh term in Ref. ",
            "section": "IV. ESTIMATING THE INFLUENCE OF \u2206\u0393",
            "paragraph_rank": 41,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "[6] has a negligible influence on the three final results of this analysis.",
            "section": "IV. ESTIMATING THE INFLUENCE OF \u2206\u0393",
            "paragraph_rank": 41,
            "section_rank": 5,
            "ref_spans": [
