        },
        {
            "text": "V. CONCLUSION",
            "section_rank": 6
        },
        {
            "text": "Using 470 \u00d7 10 6 BB events from BABAR, we determine Im (z) = 0.010 \u00b1 0.030 \u00b1 0.013 , Re (z) = \u22120.065 \u00b1 0.028 \u00b1 0.014 , |A/A| = 0.999 \u00b1 0.023 \u00b1 0.017 ,",
            "section": "V. CONCLUSION",
            "paragraph_rank": 42,
            "section_rank": 6
        },
        {
            "text": "where the first uncertainties are statistical and the second uncertainties systematic. ",
            "section": "V. CONCLUSION",
            "paragraph_rank": 43,
            "section_rank": 6
        },
        {
            "text": "All three results are compatible with CP T symmetry in B 0 -B 0 mixing and in B \u2192ccK decays. ",
            "section": "V. CONCLUSION",
            "paragraph_rank": 43,
            "section_rank": 6
        },
        {
            "text": "The uncertainties on Re (z) are comparable with those obtained by Belle in 2012 [10] with 535 \u00d7 10 6 BB events, Re (z) = \u22120.019 \u00b1 0.037 \u00b1 0.033. ",
            "section": "V. CONCLUSION",
            "paragraph_rank": 43,
            "section_rank": 6,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 80,
                    "end": 84,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b22",
                    "text": "[10]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The uncertainties on Im (z) are considerably larger, as expected, than those obtained by BABAR in 2006 [8] with di-lepton decays from 232 \u00d7 10 6 BB events, Im (z) = \u22120.014 \u00b1 0.007 \u00b1 0.003. ",
            "section": "V. CONCLUSION",
            "paragraph_rank": 43,
            "section_rank": 6,
            "ref_spans": [
